%% Diagram: GFS-style write — separate data pipeline from control flow
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Master
    participant Primary as Primary CS
    participant Sec1 as Secondary CS1
    participant Sec2 as Secondary CS2

    Client->>Master: 1. Open / AddChunk(file)
    Master->>Master: Pick replicas (rack-aware)
    Master->>Master: Grant lease to primary
    Master-->>Client: ChunkInfo{primary, secondaries, version}

    Note over Client,Sec2: Data flow — pipelined nearest-first
    Client->>Primary: 2. Push data (closest replica)
    Primary->>Sec1: 2a. Forward bytes
    Sec1->>Sec2: 2b. Forward bytes
    Note over Primary,Sec2: All replicas buffer in LRU memory

    Note over Client,Sec2: Control flow — primary serializes
    Client->>Primary: 3. WriteChunk(offset)
    Primary->>Primary: Apply locally
    Primary->>Sec1: 4. Write at offset
    Primary->>Sec2: 4. Write at offset
    Sec1-->>Primary: 5. Ack
    Sec2-->>Primary: 5. Ack
    Primary-->>Client: 6. Success (or partial failure)
